  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n0.0.0\n\n### What happened?\n\nWhen the automated GitHub Actions bot closes a 'stale' issue, and an admin for the repo reopens the issue, the issue still remains locked to previous contributors to that issue before the inital closing of the issue. \r\n\r\nsee https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/2178 as an example of a reopened issue that is closed to new comments \r\n\r\nAlso unsure if this qualifies as the proper category to file such reports as it is a 'bug' but not directly related to hardhat per se!\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\ncheck out https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/2178\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
